    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That sounds like a very \"fiscally responsible\" way of looking at it, but doesn't focusing so much on debt actually hurt people in the short term? Like, if we don't invest in education or healthcare now because we're scared of the debt, won't the economy actually suffer more because the workforce is less capable? It feels like you're saying debt reduction is the only way to be responsible.",
